    "long_description": "Kolattam (Stick Dance), also known as Kolo in some areas, is a folk dance performed in Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh, and Karnataka. Derived from 'Kol' (stick) and 'Attam' (dance), it creates rhythmic patterns by striking small wooden sticks. \n\nIt was traditionally a temple art form performed for rain or harvest. A variation, Pinnal Kolattam, involves weaving ropes hanging from a central pole while dancing, creating intricate braids.",
